WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.049 --> 00:00:09.843
Welcome to Afghanistan.

2
00:00:11.594 --> 00:00:14.431
[Emily] <i>My name is Angela Adams.</i>

3
00:00:14.514 --> 00:00:17.642
<i>I'm a special agent
with the Federal Bureau of Investigation.</i>

4
00:00:17.726 --> 00:00:19.853
Your father is Faraz Hamzad.

5
00:00:20.353 --> 00:00:22.939
<i>Your name is Parwana.</i>

6
00:00:23.732 --> 00:00:28.236
We were told that causing Hamzad trouble
wouldn't be a problem for you.

7
00:00:28.319 --> 00:00:29.946
What kind of trouble will this cause him?

8
00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:31.614
The devastating kind.

9
00:00:31.698 --> 00:00:33.158
The Meshbahar Deposit.

10
00:00:33.241 --> 00:00:37.328
[Omar] Faraz Hamzad found it.
He has plans to exploit it.

11
00:00:37.412 --> 00:00:41.374
I am looking at it as we speak.
Everything is stopped.

12
00:00:41.458 --> 00:00:43.543
There are Talib soldiers here.

13
00:00:44.627 --> 00:00:46.504
[in Dari] I am here for Hamzad.

14
00:00:47.047 --> 00:00:48.715
He does not answer to you.

15
00:00:49.215 --> 00:00:51.342
Will you be producing him.

16
00:00:51.468 --> 00:00:53.053
or will I be coming to take him?

17
00:00:53.261 --> 00:00:55.305
[Faraz. in English]
It's not safe for you here anymore.

18
00:00:55.388 --> 00:00:56.389
Where are we going?

19
00:00:56.473 --> 00:00:58.975
A cave that I once told your mother of.

20
00:00:59.059 --> 00:01:00.143
[Harper] What is this?

21
00:01:00.226 --> 00:01:02.479
[Chase] A place she could hide. Disappear.

22
00:01:06.191 --> 00:01:07.358
[Emily] What?

23
00:01:08.234 --> 00:01:09.069
[gunshot]

24
00:01:53.947 --> 00:01:54.948
[gun cocks]

25
00:01:59.744 --> 00:02:00.870
[gunshot]

26
00:02:06.334 --> 00:02:09.462
[breathes shakily. grunts]

27
00:02:19.639 --> 00:02:21.141
[groaning]

28
00:02:37.490 --> 00:02:38.741
[footsteps approaching]

29
00:03:37.008 --> 00:03:38.218
[Faraz groans]

30
00:03:43.973 --> 00:03:48.561
- [Emily panting]
- [Faraz groaning]

31
00:04:16.422 --> 00:04:18.049
- Angela...
- [Emily sobbing]

32
00:04:18.132 --> 00:04:21.928
...just be careful with him.

33
00:04:23.304 --> 00:04:25.306
[Emily breathes shakily]

34
00:04:27.517 --> 00:04:28.518
What happened?

35
00:04:30.103 --> 00:04:31.896
It wasn't easy getting this far.

36
00:04:36.818 --> 00:04:38.027
How'd you even get here?

37
00:04:39.070 --> 00:04:40.071
Marion.

38
00:04:41.322 --> 00:04:46.119
She got us in. She'll get us out.
The chopper is just a phone call away.

39
00:04:47.954 --> 00:04:49.289
It's time to go home now.

40
00:05:10.685 --> 00:05:12.603
If we leave him here. he'll die.

41
00:05:16.024 --> 00:05:17.025
Maybe.

42
00:05:19.902 --> 00:05:21.863
Well. we're not going to do that.

43
00:05:23.740 --> 00:05:24.866
[Harper] Okay. Listen...

44
00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:28.536
We have a lot to talk about.
but we have to get him home.

45
00:05:29.704 --> 00:05:31.956
They need him there.
and he's not going to make it alone.

46
00:05:33.583 --> 00:05:35.877
I'm needed home too.

47
00:05:36.711 --> 00:05:39.589
Because of him. Because of what he did.
I know you know that.

48
00:05:39.672 --> 00:05:40.590
[grunts]

49
00:05:40.673 --> 00:05:42.842
I told you not to come.

50
00:05:45.053 --> 00:05:46.179
What?

51
00:05:46.262 --> 00:05:50.183
[Emily] I told you to look after
Cheryl and Henry. and not me.

52
00:05:50.266 --> 00:05:51.392
[Chase] Em.

53
00:05:51.476 --> 00:05:54.520
Em. he came here
only because he loves you.

54
00:05:54.604 --> 00:05:57.732
And what happened just now.
that was to protect me.

55
00:05:57.815 --> 00:05:58.983
Does he know?

56
00:06:01.194 --> 00:06:02.487
[stammers] What do you mean?

57
00:06:05.948 --> 00:06:09.952
Did you tell him what I am?

58
00:06:11.788 --> 00:06:12.789
I did. yeah.

59
00:06:15.500 --> 00:06:18.503
Well. then this shouldn't be hard
for either of you to understand.

60
00:06:21.381 --> 00:06:23.591
I can't leave him here to die.

61
00:06:25.134 --> 00:06:26.552
And I'm asking you to help me.

62
00:06:28.888 --> 00:06:29.889
[Faraz] It's time.

63
00:06:32.642 --> 00:06:33.935
It's time for you to go.

64
00:06:34.811 --> 00:06:36.020
We both know that.

65
00:06:36.687 --> 00:06:39.399
No. not like this. Not with you like this.

66
00:06:43.069 --> 00:06:44.237
You have to go.

67
00:06:47.156 --> 00:06:49.367
There's government soldiers in his house.

68
00:06:49.450 --> 00:06:51.577
They've come for him.
but they're there because of me.

69
00:06:52.745 --> 00:06:53.830
They're looking for me.

70
00:06:54.914 --> 00:06:57.041
The family. everyone there.
they're in danger.

71
00:06:57.125 --> 00:06:58.251
They need him.

72
00:06:59.502 --> 00:07:01.254
And I'm going to get him back there.

73
00:07:03.464 --> 00:07:06.426
Are you going to help me?

74
00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:11.431
Yes.

75
00:07:12.849 --> 00:07:14.016
[sighs]

76
00:07:25.069 --> 00:07:27.238
Excuse me. but what the fuck?

77
00:07:27.321 --> 00:07:30.116
- What?
- We're taking him home?

78
00:07:30.199 --> 00:07:31.909
Isn't that awfully nice of us?

79
00:07:31.993 --> 00:07:34.162
Maybe we didn't hear
the same thing just now.

80
00:07:35.538 --> 00:07:38.749
Something happened between them.

81
00:07:39.375 --> 00:07:42.086
I don't know what it is or what it means.

82
00:07:42.170 --> 00:07:44.714
But I'm telling you.
what I heard is that if we were

83
00:07:44.797 --> 00:07:47.341
to leave him up there to die.
we'll have lost her forever.

84
00:07:47.425 --> 00:07:50.553
Lost her forever?
Are you being serious right now?

85
00:07:50.636 --> 00:07:51.762
Harold. I'm telling you.

86
00:07:52.305 --> 00:07:54.640
that is what I heard
and I'm not willing to risk it.

87
00:07:54.724 --> 00:07:55.725
So. yes.

88
00:07:56.642 --> 00:07:58.227
we're taking him home.

89
00:07:59.520 --> 00:08:00.521
Jesus.

90
00:08:01.147 --> 00:08:02.523
You're terrified of her.

91
00:08:03.524 --> 00:08:05.860
You were so sure she was dead.
Was it because

92
00:08:05.943 --> 00:08:07.904
- the alternative is even scarier?
- No.

93
00:08:17.830 --> 00:08:20.917
[in Dari] You are not the first
to come for him.

94
00:08:22.126 --> 00:08:25.505
Not the first to see a moment where
there seems to be an opportunity.

95
00:08:26.547 --> 00:08:31.552
Where he seems weakened...

96
00:08:31.761 --> 00:08:33.554
I assure you...

97
00:08:34.138 --> 00:08:36.807
he only seems that way.

98
00:08:38.351 --> 00:08:39.352
[in Dari] I have nothing to say to you...

99
00:08:41.687 --> 00:08:44.315
my patience is wearing thin.

100
00:08:45.525 --> 00:08:47.276
If he were here...

101
00:08:47.401 --> 00:08:49.153
he would be far less understanding than I...

102
00:08:49.278 --> 00:08:50.279
I assure you.

103
00:08:50.488 --> 00:08:54.617
If you had the leverage
you seem to think you do...

104
00:08:55.159 --> 00:08:57.203
I would have been recalled by now.

105
00:08:57.537 --> 00:08:59.205
I would have been arrested.

106
00:09:00.831 --> 00:09:02.917
[helicopter whirring]

107
00:09:15.179 --> 00:09:16.389
Who is that?

108
00:10:10.735 --> 00:10:11.819
[speaking French] <i>Français?</i>

109
00:10:16.240 --> 00:10:17.325
[sighs]

110
00:10:18.075 --> 00:10:19.076
[in English] English then.

111
00:10:21.495 --> 00:10:22.705
You're an intelligence officer.

112
00:10:22.788 --> 00:10:25.124
You speak something
your men won't understand. no?

113
00:10:27.126 --> 00:10:28.127
Who are you?

114
00:10:29.045 --> 00:10:30.296
I'm very glad you asked.

115
00:10:31.339 --> 00:10:33.716
It means you have no idea
what you just stumbled into.

116
00:10:34.717 --> 00:10:38.095
No idea how important
Faraz Hamzad's commerce is to Kabul.

117
00:10:38.721 --> 00:10:40.264
No idea the role I play in it.

118
00:10:40.973 --> 00:10:43.434
No idea how much trouble you are in.

119
00:10:44.977 --> 00:10:45.978
Come here.

120
00:10:46.854 --> 00:10:49.774
The Ministry was concerned
because our last transfer was delayed.

121
00:10:50.483 --> 00:10:52.902
The sanctions you are under
are complicated.

122
00:10:53.402 --> 00:10:56.322
We are doing the best we can
to stay ahead of them. but we stumbled.

123
00:10:57.406 --> 00:11:00.201
The Ministry allowed you to come up here
to harass us because of it.

124
00:11:00.284 --> 00:11:05.039
but this will assure them
there is nothing to be concerned about.

125
00:11:07.917 --> 00:11:10.336
They used you to send a message to us.

126
00:11:11.212 --> 00:11:12.588
This money is my reply.

127
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:15.424
And the matter is closed.

128
00:11:17.385 --> 00:11:19.679
Anything more you do from here.
you will answer for.

129
00:11:21.222 --> 00:11:22.223
I promise.

130
00:11:28.145 --> 00:11:29.146
Leave.

131
00:11:37.238 --> 00:11:40.241
[chattering]

132
00:11:50.751 --> 00:11:52.253
Where did you get this money?

133
00:11:53.212 --> 00:11:54.213
You don't wanna know.

134
00:11:54.714 --> 00:11:55.798
[in Dari] Yes I do.

135
00:11:55.881 --> 00:11:58.509
[in English] Mother. we have
bigger problems than that right now.

136
00:11:58.592 --> 00:12:00.720
What could be bigger problems than this?

137
00:12:04.265 --> 00:12:06.684
Have you ever heard of a man
named Morgan Bote?

138
00:12:08.644 --> 00:12:11.313
He is the one who was behind the deal
to deliver Dan Chase.

139
00:12:12.356 --> 00:12:16.110
And it would seem he is the one
who was so angry we took Parwana instead.

140
00:12:16.777 --> 00:12:20.239
he's frozen all our assets
and means to see us ruined over it.

141
00:12:22.783 --> 00:12:24.785
[people chattering]

142
00:13:14.960 --> 00:13:16.170
[in Dari] Wait.

143
00:13:21.133 --> 00:13:22.676
What's your name?

144
00:13:24.261 --> 00:13:25.262
Hmm?

145
00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:28.432
It's ok.

146
00:13:28.557 --> 00:13:30.726
I just want to ask you a question.

147
00:13:31.560 --> 00:13:33.604
Farouk! Farouk!

148
00:13:33.687 --> 00:13:35.940
[in Dari] What do you want from my son?

149
00:13:42.488 --> 00:13:43.322
[sobbing] Farouk...

150
00:13:43.405 --> 00:13:46.951
Have you seen anyone new here recently?

151
00:13:47.910 --> 00:13:49.161
A woman...

152
00:13:49.245 --> 00:13:50.496
Farouk.

153
00:13:57.044 --> 00:13:58.921
Ok... I see...

154
00:14:02.967 --> 00:14:05.886
This woman can't speak our language.
can she?

155
00:14:10.015 --> 00:14:11.892
Do you know her name?

156
00:14:14.478 --> 00:14:15.980
Can you tell me her name?

157
00:14:16.063 --> 00:14:18.274
- [grunts]
- [soldiers clamoring]

158
00:14:18.357 --> 00:14:21.068
[screaming] Farouk! Farouk!

159
00:14:21.569 --> 00:14:24.196
- Farouk! Farouk!
- [gun fires]

160
00:14:27.157 --> 00:14:28.158
- [people screaming]
- [gasps]

161
00:14:29.994 --> 00:14:30.828
[pants]

162
00:14:38.127 --> 00:14:41.213
[guns firing]

163
00:15:34.600 --> 00:15:37.853
Probably could have parked
someplace a little less public.

164
00:15:43.108 --> 00:15:47.071
Ask me what you want to ask me.

165
00:15:51.909 --> 00:15:53.410
What did you say to her?

166
00:15:54.161 --> 00:15:55.162
[chuckles]

167
00:15:57.456 --> 00:16:01.001
You had a lifetime to tell her your story.

168
00:16:01.085 --> 00:16:06.090
And now you're concerned I might
have had the nerve to tell her mine.

169
00:16:06.799 --> 00:16:08.008
[chuckles]

170
00:16:10.970 --> 00:16:12.554
What did you say to her?

171
00:16:17.226 --> 00:16:18.978
You can stay concerned.

172
00:16:25.526 --> 00:16:29.822
- I'm gonna head down.
- Oh. no. no. I'm fine. I'll handle it.

173
00:16:30.948 --> 00:16:33.534
- I don't think that's a good idea.
- I'd feel better if you stayed back here.

174
00:17:01.812 --> 00:17:03.397
- All right. listen.
- No.

175
00:17:04.189 --> 00:17:05.649
You don't even know what I'm gonna say.

176
00:17:05.733 --> 00:17:09.695
I know that if it starts with. "Listen."
I can't deal with it right now.

177
00:17:09.778 --> 00:17:11.989
Okay? I know what's going on in your head.
We're way too...

178
00:17:13.365 --> 00:17:15.159
What? We're way too what?

179
00:17:17.161 --> 00:17:18.871
I was gonna say we're way too alike.

180
00:17:21.665 --> 00:17:23.459
I don't know what's happening to me
right now. okay?

181
00:17:23.542 --> 00:17:25.252
- I need you to understand that.
- I do.

182
00:17:25.335 --> 00:17:26.336
- No. you don't.
- I do.

183
00:17:26.420 --> 00:17:27.504
No. You can't.

184
00:17:30.632 --> 00:17:34.595
But getting him home.
that's important to me.

185
00:17:37.639 --> 00:17:39.725
And I need it to be important to you
right now.

186
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:47.733
All right.

187
00:17:48.776 --> 00:17:49.902
Stay behind me.

188
00:17:51.195 --> 00:17:52.362
I know what I'm doing.

189
00:17:52.446 --> 00:17:55.407
Of course you do.
I want you to stay behind me anyway.

190
00:17:57.242 --> 00:17:59.203
That's important to me right now.

191
00:18:04.249 --> 00:18:06.794
A special forces chopper?

192
00:18:06.877 --> 00:18:09.630
[Marion] <i>I have an associate
who has influence with Tashkent.</i>

193
00:18:10.214 --> 00:18:14.093
<i>They will enter Afghan airspace.
proceed to a location you designate</i>

194
00:18:14.176 --> 00:18:17.387
<i>to collect three passengers.
and return back across the border.</i>

195
00:18:18.138 --> 00:18:21.225
I can't imagine how much that cost you
with your associate.

196
00:18:22.017 --> 00:18:23.894
<i>More than what it will cost you with me.</i>

197
00:18:25.979 --> 00:18:29.483
I told you I'm in no position
to offer you anything you would want.

198
00:18:30.192 --> 00:18:31.193
Not anymore.

199
00:18:31.735 --> 00:18:33.570
<i>Dinner is what you'll owe me.</i>

200
00:18:34.196 --> 00:18:35.447
Yeah. Okay.

201
00:18:36.240 --> 00:18:40.202
Listen. whatever it actually is
you imagine I'm into you for for this.

202
00:18:40.285 --> 00:18:43.372
I assure you. you can forget it.

203
00:18:43.455 --> 00:18:45.791
<i>The chopper will not want
to be inside Afghan airspace</i>

204
00:18:45.874 --> 00:18:47.084
<i>any longer than necessary.</i>

205
00:18:47.167 --> 00:18:49.586
<i>and they will not want
to be noticed at all.</i>

206
00:18:49.670 --> 00:18:52.714
<i>Try not to cause
an international incident. Please.</i>

207
00:18:53.298 --> 00:18:54.299
[line clicks]

208
00:19:02.224 --> 00:19:06.436
[Omar. in Dari. through speaker]
You might yet still survive this.

209
00:19:07.521 --> 00:19:10.566
You owe nothing to Faraz Hamzad...

210
00:19:10.649 --> 00:19:15.737
who has made you all a target
through his crimes.

211
00:19:17.072 --> 00:19:18.657
The choice...

212
00:19:19.658 --> 00:19:21.827
belongs to you.

213
00:19:27.416 --> 00:19:30.043
[in English] What if we were
to call the minister directly?

214
00:19:31.461 --> 00:19:33.255
We fired on his soldiers.

215
00:19:34.173 --> 00:19:36.091
I fear we are past phone calls.

216
00:19:37.467 --> 00:19:41.054
And even if we hadn't.
this man. Morgan Bote.

217
00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:43.599
he has somehow managed
to freeze everything.

218
00:19:44.474 --> 00:19:46.977
The US accounts. the offshore accounts.

219
00:19:47.060 --> 00:19:48.812
Our money and the promise of more of it

220
00:19:48.896 --> 00:19:51.732
once the Meshbahar Deposit
is fully operational

221
00:19:51.815 --> 00:19:53.609
were what held the Taliban at bay.

222
00:19:54.443 --> 00:19:57.196
But without it. we are defenseless.

223
00:20:01.074 --> 00:20:02.784
There had to have been a better way.

224
00:20:03.285 --> 00:20:06.246
If you would have asked me.
I would have helped to find a better way.

225
00:20:07.581 --> 00:20:09.917
I promise. if one of the two of us
should be angry

226
00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:11.376
about how this was mishandled.

227
00:20:11.877 --> 00:20:13.045
it isn't you.

228
00:20:22.971 --> 00:20:25.349
[in Dari] He didn't want anyone to know...

229
00:20:27.851 --> 00:20:30.062
until she was here safely.

230
00:20:32.689 --> 00:20:35.234
[in English] I get it. I do.

231
00:20:37.110 --> 00:20:38.403
But the cost of that.

232
00:20:38.904 --> 00:20:40.906
we are only beginning
to know what it'll be.

233
00:20:55.254 --> 00:20:57.965
[speaking Dari]

234
00:20:58.840 --> 00:20:59.675
[in Dari] Yes...

235
00:21:01.343 --> 00:21:02.469
standing by...

236
00:21:02.594 --> 00:21:03.470
yes...

237
00:21:14.606 --> 00:21:15.983
[rustling]

238
00:21:17.234 --> 00:21:18.902
Did you hear that?

239
00:21:18.986 --> 00:21:20.487
[grunting]

240
00:21:23.073 --> 00:21:25.784
[both straining]

241
00:21:31.748 --> 00:21:33.250
[choking]

242
00:21:48.098 --> 00:21:50.267
[grunts]

243
00:22:29.306 --> 00:22:30.974
[radio static. beeps]

244
00:22:32.225 --> 00:22:34.394
[soldier. in Dari]
Report back to your position. please.

245
00:22:38.106 --> 00:22:41.193
Report back to your position. please.

246
00:22:46.448 --> 00:22:48.367
Still no response...

247
00:22:49.785 --> 00:22:52.287
do we have his last position?

248
00:22:54.289 --> 00:22:55.374
Check again!

249
00:22:55.499 --> 00:22:56.625
[Faraz] I am here.

250
00:23:02.005 --> 00:23:03.048
I see.

251
00:23:05.175 --> 00:23:10.055
Perhaps if you'd been here instead
to speak for yourself...

252
00:23:10.180 --> 00:23:12.224
things wouldn't have gotten
so out of hand.

253
00:23:13.809 --> 00:23:16.311
Let me make this simple for you.

254
00:23:17.229 --> 00:23:19.272
Show yourself here...

255
00:23:19.481 --> 00:23:22.567
and I will take you
to the Ministry in Kabul myself...

256
00:23:22.692 --> 00:23:26.530
where you can explain
who the American woman is...

257
00:23:26.780 --> 00:23:29.950
why two Americans tried
to rescue her alone...

258
00:23:30.409 --> 00:23:34.996
and why they should be expected
to trust you.

259
00:23:35.247 --> 00:23:37.207
Decide quickly...

260
00:23:37.457 --> 00:23:39.918
or things here will only get uglier.

261
00:23:41.294 --> 00:23:42.421
[in English] We must go.

262
00:23:43.046 --> 00:23:44.506
- To Kabul?
- Yeah.

263
00:23:44.589 --> 00:23:45.924
That can't be safe for you.

264
00:23:46.007 --> 00:23:47.092
[Faraz] Safe?

265
00:23:47.592 --> 00:23:49.261
It's not important what happens to me.

266
00:23:50.345 --> 00:23:52.472
What matters is that our people are safe.

267
00:23:53.014 --> 00:23:55.142
- We must go.
- She's right.

268
00:23:55.225 --> 00:23:58.520
If you go back there like this.
he's gonna kill you.

269
00:23:58.603 --> 00:24:01.106
and then he's gonna take
whatever he wants anyway.

270
00:24:01.690 --> 00:24:02.941
Who are you?

271
00:24:06.403 --> 00:24:09.489
Who are you to have an opinion

272
00:24:09.573 --> 00:24:13.910
of what is best for me
and the people I lead?

273
00:24:14.828 --> 00:24:18.665
Who are you that I should account for it?

274
00:24:19.291 --> 00:24:20.750
And since you're asking.

275
00:24:20.834 --> 00:24:22.502
I'm the guy who's going out of his way

276
00:24:22.586 --> 00:24:25.672
to make sure you don't fall off your horse
and die on your way home.

277
00:24:25.755 --> 00:24:29.176
And if you think that earns you
a position with me.

278
00:24:29.259 --> 00:24:33.597
that services a debt you imagine
might be repaid.

279
00:24:34.639 --> 00:24:36.600
you are terribly mistaken.

280
00:24:38.310 --> 00:24:40.187
- What if I went with you?
- What?

281
00:24:40.270 --> 00:24:42.272
All the way into the village with you.

282
00:24:42.355 --> 00:24:44.816
- Why on Earth would you do that?
- So I can diffuse all of this.

283
00:24:44.900 --> 00:24:46.818
How on Earth would you do that?

284
00:24:46.902 --> 00:24:48.737
- With the truth.
- Emily.

285
00:24:48.820 --> 00:24:52.282
The man on the radio wants to know
why you kidnapped an FBI agent.

286
00:24:52.365 --> 00:24:54.576
But there is no FBI agent here.

287
00:24:55.076 --> 00:24:57.954
There is no Angela Adams anymore.

288
00:24:58.038 --> 00:25:00.332
I mean. how could there be
after all of this?

289
00:25:01.124 --> 00:25:03.543
The truth is. I was born here
and I was taken away.

290
00:25:04.044 --> 00:25:05.837
This is a family story.

291
00:25:05.921 --> 00:25:08.173
Nothing that could
possibly be compromising to you.

292
00:25:09.174 --> 00:25:12.052
- No. No.
- [Emily] Why not?

293
00:25:13.303 --> 00:25:16.181
The Taliban's secret police
are not exactly known

294
00:25:16.806 --> 00:25:19.059
for their readiness to listen to reason.

295
00:25:19.142 --> 00:25:21.978
[Emily] I don't care if he likes it.
He just needs to worry that...

296
00:25:22.062 --> 00:25:24.814
that he has a weaker hand
than the one he thought he was holding.

297
00:25:24.898 --> 00:25:26.233
He'd kill you.

298
00:25:31.154 --> 00:25:32.322
[Faraz] I did this.

299
00:25:38.203 --> 00:25:39.663
I opened this door.

300
00:25:40.956 --> 00:25:43.875
And the danger that has resulted...

301
00:25:45.085 --> 00:25:46.836
It will not fall upon you.

302
00:25:48.630 --> 00:25:50.131
I will not permit it.

303
00:26:33.800 --> 00:26:35.093
[Harper] You warned me.

304
00:26:35.176 --> 00:26:36.177
What's that?

305
00:26:38.346 --> 00:26:40.932
"There's no Angela Adams anymore."

306
00:26:42.225 --> 00:26:43.310
You warned me.

307
00:26:44.936 --> 00:26:47.022
That if I wasn't careful with her

308
00:26:48.064 --> 00:26:49.316
in that moment.

309
00:26:49.983 --> 00:26:51.610
then she'd disappear on me.

310
00:26:51.693 --> 00:26:53.862
I didn't imagine it would happen
the same morning.

311
00:26:53.945 --> 00:26:56.072
No. I don't think she meant it that way.

312
00:26:57.324 --> 00:26:58.992
I don't think that was about you.

313
00:26:59.075 --> 00:27:00.577
It was a little about me.

314
00:27:01.286 --> 00:27:03.079
I just came halfway around the world

315
00:27:03.580 --> 00:27:06.041
to save a person
who doesn't want to exist anymore.

316
00:27:06.791 --> 00:27:09.628
Would you have done anything different
if you had known that?

317
00:27:10.337 --> 00:27:12.380
You're such an asshole. Of course not.

318
00:27:13.757 --> 00:27:15.925
But I'm not thrilled about how it feels.

319
00:27:17.677 --> 00:27:21.473
- And I'm trying to talk to you about...
- Jesus. fine. Okay.

320
00:27:21.556 --> 00:27:24.309
You should have listened to me
when I warned you.

321
00:27:25.101 --> 00:27:26.102
Better?

322
00:27:27.312 --> 00:27:28.480
[chuckles]

323
00:27:29.022 --> 00:27:30.982
It's not like she had a say in the matter.

324
00:27:31.066 --> 00:27:35.820
It's not like Angela Adams is gonna show
up again for work on Monday after this.

325
00:27:36.613 --> 00:27:39.949
I guess I thought there might be a way

326
00:27:40.700 --> 00:27:44.079
that we would fight to save the name

327
00:27:45.080 --> 00:27:46.081
somehow.

328
00:27:46.164 --> 00:27:48.917
since it was so important to both of us.

329
00:27:52.379 --> 00:27:54.839
I suppose I should be angry. but that kid.

330
00:27:55.799 --> 00:27:57.801
she came halfway around the world

331
00:27:57.884 --> 00:27:59.928
to find answers
that no one else would give her.

332
00:28:00.428 --> 00:28:03.431
so she could stare the truth in the eyes.

333
00:28:03.973 --> 00:28:06.434
And in the moment
when I tried to pull rank

334
00:28:06.518 --> 00:28:08.144
and make her feel guilty about it.

335
00:28:09.354 --> 00:28:12.899
she stared me dead in the eyes
and told me to go fuck myself.

336
00:28:15.777 --> 00:28:20.240
How could you not be
at least a little proud of her?

337
00:28:22.659 --> 00:28:24.536
He can say what he wants about you.

338
00:28:26.246 --> 00:28:27.706
You raised a hell of a kid.

339
00:28:52.313 --> 00:28:53.982
The entrance is sealed.

340
00:28:55.442 --> 00:28:56.985
There's no way in the front door.

341
00:28:59.279 --> 00:29:01.281
- You're gonna have to go...
- [Faraz] No.

342
00:29:01.364 --> 00:29:03.825
I will not steal into my own home

343
00:29:05.535 --> 00:29:06.953
through secret doors.

344
00:29:08.413 --> 00:29:10.039
I will face them where they are.

345
00:29:13.460 --> 00:29:14.878
Please don't.

346
00:29:16.254 --> 00:29:18.214
I'm sorry it was this way.

347
00:29:19.841 --> 00:29:21.509
but I'm not sorry

348
00:29:22.010 --> 00:29:23.887
that now you have seen this place.

349
00:29:25.138 --> 00:29:27.348
and it has seen you.

350
00:29:43.239 --> 00:29:44.824
They're gonna kill him. aren't they?

351
00:29:48.369 --> 00:29:50.580
[Harper] Our ride is gonna be
getting here awful soon.

352
00:29:51.080 --> 00:29:52.749
If we're gonna get out of here.

353
00:29:52.832 --> 00:29:55.543
I gotta let them know
where we're gonna meet.

354
00:29:58.129 --> 00:30:01.299
[Chase] Yeah. You should call 'em.

355
00:30:21.110 --> 00:30:22.946
[soldiers shouting in Dari]

356
00:30:36.793 --> 00:30:37.794
[grunts]

357
00:30:50.473 --> 00:30:52.475
[in Dari] It didn't have to be this way.

358
00:30:53.351 --> 00:30:56.104
You could've made this so much easier.

359
00:30:58.565 --> 00:31:00.358
Are you coming with me...

360
00:31:00.775 --> 00:31:05.280
or will we be forced to finish
what your people started?

361
00:31:06.739 --> 00:31:09.784
[soldiers clamoring]

362
00:31:28.177 --> 00:31:29.929
They won't set down here.

363
00:31:30.597 --> 00:31:32.098
Not with all the activity.

364
00:31:32.682 --> 00:31:34.559
We'll hump over the ridge here.

365
00:31:35.727 --> 00:31:37.020
How much time we have?

366
00:31:37.896 --> 00:31:40.773
Not much. They won't wait long.

367
00:31:43.651 --> 00:31:46.988
Emily. Emily! Emily. no!

368
00:31:48.573 --> 00:31:51.910
Yeah. change of plans.
We need to redirect. Now.

369
00:31:51.993 --> 00:31:53.578
[soldiers chattering]

370
00:32:10.511 --> 00:32:12.013
[chattering stops]

371
00:32:47.423 --> 00:32:48.466
Hello there.

372
00:32:49.968 --> 00:32:51.844
[Faraz panting]

373
00:32:57.809 --> 00:32:59.769
Would you like to tell me who you are?

374
00:33:07.193 --> 00:33:08.403
Don't worry about them.

375
00:33:09.362 --> 00:33:13.199
In a few moments.
he will be coming with me.

376
00:33:13.282 --> 00:33:16.577
He won't get everyone killed
to prevent this.

377
00:33:17.787 --> 00:33:20.206
So. at this point.

378
00:33:21.082 --> 00:33:24.585
this is just for the sake
of my own curiosity.

379
00:33:27.922 --> 00:33:29.966
You are the abducted American.

380
00:33:30.049 --> 00:33:31.843
The one who started all of this mess.

381
00:33:33.511 --> 00:33:34.554
Yes?

382
00:33:42.812 --> 00:33:47.316
You're an agent with the FBI.

383
00:33:49.110 --> 00:33:50.236
This is also true?

384
00:33:54.741 --> 00:33:57.118
If you tell me. it might help.

385
00:33:57.785 --> 00:34:00.788
I might be willing to make this
just a little easier on everyone

386
00:34:00.872 --> 00:34:05.877
if I didn't have to end the day
still wondering what it is I'm missing.

387
00:34:07.170 --> 00:34:08.921
You don't belong here.

388
00:34:12.300 --> 00:34:15.553
This doesn't need to be your fight.

389
00:34:18.598 --> 00:34:19.599
Just tell me.

390
00:34:22.894 --> 00:34:23.936
Who are you?

391
00:34:53.549 --> 00:34:59.680
My name is Parwana Hamzad.

392
00:35:03.142 --> 00:35:04.602
[both grunting]

393
00:35:04.685 --> 00:35:06.270
[shots firing]

394
00:35:26.958 --> 00:35:29.210
"On whose authority?" On my authority.

395
00:35:30.461 --> 00:35:32.755
Yeah. but you can't evac us if we're dead!

396
00:35:32.839 --> 00:35:35.466
I'm on the hook for this.
Just do it! You understand?

397
00:35:35.550 --> 00:35:36.884
[line clicks]

398
00:35:36.968 --> 00:35:38.052
Hello?

399
00:35:42.849 --> 00:35:44.350
[shots continue]

400
00:35:44.433 --> 00:35:46.352
[people clamoring]

401
00:36:02.618 --> 00:36:05.288
[helicopter whirring]

402
00:36:11.335 --> 00:36:12.837
- [Emily screams]
- [Faraz grunts]

403
00:36:14.463 --> 00:36:15.798
[screams]

404
00:36:55.546 --> 00:36:58.007
[straining. gurgling]

405
00:37:09.936 --> 00:37:11.604
[Omar breathing shakily]

406
00:37:21.822 --> 00:37:22.823
[straining stops]
